       int wctob(wint_t c);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       wctob  determines whether c corresponds to a member of the
       extended character set whose multibyte character represen-
       tation  is  as  a  single  byte  when in the initial shift
       state.

   RReettuurrnn vvaalluueess
       wctob returns EOF if c does not correspond to a  multibyte
       character  with length one; otherwise, it returns the sin-
       gle byte representation.

